- Install Flask SQLAlchemy --> create database (similar to Django orm)
  - pip install flask_sqlalchemy mysqlclient --> db created

- create a file --> app.py
- in app.py
  - from flask import Flask, request, jsonify
  - from flask_sqlalchemy import SQLAlchemy

 - alembic --> pip install alembic --> enables you to make changes in runtime like adding a col mobile 
  - create 
    - app.py 
    - config.py
    - models.py

- cd alembic_practice --> go to your folder 
- alembic init migrations --> creates migrations, alembic.ini file 
  - inside migrations --> vesrion (folder) and env.py

- make change in your alembic.ini file --> sqlalchemy.url = mysql://root:root@localhost/b14_flask

- env.py
  - from models import db
  - target_metadata = db.metadata

- alembic revision --autogenerate -m "create employees table" --> willcreate a file that has a db code ready converted from model
 - before running above commands:
  - pip install flask_alchemy
  - pip install pymysql
  - pip install mysqlclient

- alembic upgrade head --> to push the migrations into db --> in version,a file is created 
  upgrade code will be pushed from that file into db

- alembic downgrade base --> deleted the table 

- alembic revision --autogenerate -m "create department table" --> made changes in Employee model and create department model

- alembic downgrade -1 --> go back 1 migration

- alembic downgrade -1 --> take 1 more step back 

- alembic downgrade -4 --> go back by 4 steps etc.

- alembic upgrade head --> all the availablke migrations will be pushed to db

- jwt authentication 
  - pip install flask-jwt-extended

- flask restx
  - pip install flas_restx
  - app.py, models.py, config.py , requirement.txt
  - pip freeze > requirements.txt --> creates the file
  - pip install > requirements.txt --> to install the file

- flask run --> open url --> http://127.0.0.1:5000
- flask run --dubug --> automatically restrtas the server, changes will be reflected


